) bearing distinct inversely drop-shaped median notch. Metanepisterna and metepimera narrow, in intact specimens covered by elytra.

Elytra (
Figs 1
, 
9
) oval, strongly convex, lacking humeral calli and basal impressions, each with two asetose rudiments of basal foveae (
Fig. 7
; 
bef
).

Aedeagus (
Figs 14–17
) elongate, thin-walled, with symmetrical median lobe and symmetrical, weakly sclerotized endophallus; parameres free and thick, lacking long setae.

Spermatheca (
Fig. 18
) globular, asymmetrical, moderately thick-walled.
